9. TTL (Time To Live)
TTL = 300 seconds

Means

Keep DNS result for

5 minutes

After TTL expires

↓

Ask DNS again.

TTL Tradeoff
Small TTL

Fresh Data

↓

More DNS Queries

--------------------------

Large TTL

Faster

↓

Old Cache

Interview Question:

Why doesn't Google use TTL = 1 year?

Because changing server IPs would take a year to propagate.

